.TH dot-install 1 "02 FEB 2017" "version 1.0"

.SH NAME
dot-install - Install system / application packages

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dot
.RB install
.RB [type]
.I package

.SS Types:
.TP
.BI brew " package"
install package using brew
.TP
.BI cask " package"
install package using cask
.TP
.BI code " package"
install package using VSCode
.TP
.BI mas " package"
install package using Mac App Store

.SH DESCRIPTION
This command installs a package and updates the relevant dotfile when the command
succeeds. Packages and modules are installed from various sources, see types for more
information regarding source of install.

A
.B package
is:
.IP \[bu] 2
A brew package
.IP \[bu] 2
A cask package
.IP \[bu] 2
A vscode package
.IP \[bu] 2
A Mac App Store app

